attachments.title: Band Dale Earnhardt Jr. Jr. drops ‘Dale Earnhardt’ from name
attachments.text:
DETROIT — The band “Dale Earnhardt Jr. Jr.” is dropping Dale Earnhardt from their name.
The Detroit News reported that the Detroit based indie-pop electronic duo will now be known as “JR JR.”
The band said that the name has caused much confusion, with people showing up to their concerts expecting to see the famous NASCAR driver.
The musicians said they will continue to sell shirts with their old name until the shipment runs out. The transition to a new name will be gradual.
Dale Earnhardt Jr. originally gave the band his blessing to use the name.
